-- Argentina Says Operations of British Oil Companies Is Illegal
-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 2012-06-04T11:21:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-04/argentina-says-operations-of-british-oil-companies-is-illegal.html
Argentina said five British  oil
companies  are illegally operating near the Falklands Islands,
according to a resolution in today’s official gazette.  The companies  Borders & Southern Petroleum Plc (BOR) ,  Rockhopper
Exploration Plc (RKH) ,  Desire Petroleum Plc (DES) , Argos Resources Ltd and
 Falkland Oil and Gas Ltd  don’t have the required permits to
operate in the area, which belong to Argentina, according to the
statement.  -- Editors: Dale Crofts  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in  Buenos Aires  at 
 crusso15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
